{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"jolty-stain-upturn","description":"## Why\n\nPass-2 (validate each finding) is the strongest reuse candidate: the binary sub-questions\n(`is_verifiable`, `evidence_entails_finding`, `path_reachable`, `impact_follows_necessarily`,\n`no_viable_alternative_explanation`, `no_existing_mitigation`, `severity_claim_justified` + the\ncited-reference veto) and the severity-attribute enums are properties of *a finding*, not of\nplans-vs-diffs — so a code-review finding and a plan finding answer the SAME questions. Extracting\nit gives one binary vocabulary + one `verification` contract that every gate shares, eliminating\nthe silent-drift class. The verify orchestration already built for plan-review (token-budget\nchunking, merge-by-global-index, the non-frontier verifier-model default) is likewise general and\nmoves with it.\n\n## What\n\n- Move the Pass-2 verifier into the kernel as `verify_findings(findings, *, context, model,\n  headroom) -> verifications`, carrying the chunking + merge-by-index + verifier-model resolution.\n- Make the `verification` pydantic/JSON contract the SINGLE registered source of the binary\n  vocabulary + severity-attribute enums (one schema, small/flat).\n- Reliability: validate with the existing tolerant stack (json-repair + bounded retry +\n  pydantic-ai native outputs) and DEGRADE to INDETERMINATE on an unparseable turn — never\n  hard-crash a gate. (Reuse `gate_dispatch`'s degrade path; do not add stricter validation.)\n- Rewire the plan-review verify step to consume the kernel (the per-gate verify-prompt preamble +\n  the plan context are passed in). No behavior change.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope: the Pass-2 verify function + the `verification` contract + the tolerant-validation\nreliability behavior, moved to the kernel; plan-review consumes it. Out of scope: Pass-3 (WS1, on\nwhich this depends), the coach (WS3), the seam doc + behavioral evals (WS4). Touches\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py` (verify builders), `sizing.py` (chunker), `workflow_ops.py`\n(verify-inputs op), the verify prompt(s), and the kernel module.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The kernel exposes a `verify_findings` Pass-2 entry that takes a findings list + a domain\n      context and returns the per-finding `{severity_attributes, binary}` verifications, with the\n      token-budget chunking + merge-by-global-index + verifier-model default carried over.\n- [ ] The `verification` contract is the single registered source of the binary-question\n      vocabulary + severity-attribute enums (one schema; no second copy).\n- [ ] Validation uses json-repair + bounded retry and degrades to INDETERMINATE (never crashes a\n      gate) on an unparseable structured turn; a test exercises the degrade path.\n- [ ] The plan-review verify step consumes the kernel; an offline (FakeRunner) test asserts the\n      verifications + downstream verdict are unchanged vs before.\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make check` + the full test suite pass.\n","id":"0b69-6a61-2c50-42c8","parent_id":"3316-252f-e945-4521","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS2: Extract Pass-2 finding-verifier + the verification contract into the kernel"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782607434212951001,"uuid":"073a37ab-b355-414d-bf92-a6e8a6a174a5"}